    <p style="font-weight: 800; color: #000; font-family: Georgia">Current Work</p>
    <p>I am very privileged to work with <a href="https://sites.umiacs.umd.edu/elm/"> Dr. Niklas Elmqvist</a> as a 
       research assistant.
       I focus on taking advantage of modern devices including large wall-mounted and tabletop displays, as well as portable devices, to support collaborative visual sensemaking. To this end, I have developed systems that enable cross-device interaction for visualization including <a href="http://www.umiacs.umd.edu/~elm/projects/munin/munin.pdf">Munin</a> and <a href="http://www.umiacs.umd.edu/~elm/projects/polychrome/polychrome.pdf">PolyChrome</a>, and designed natural interaction styles for large display spaces (e.g., based on body movement and hand gestures).
       I received a Masters degree from Purdue University with a thesis in computer engineering titled "Developing Digital Media Platforms for Early Design". 
       This work incidentally combines my interest in direct-touch tablets and sketching. 
       My research interests have evolved over time and a unified summary of my current research directions
       can be found <a href="/data/Badam-proposal.pdf">here</a>.
       
